title: These two cards actually the same card?

posts.post_title: These two cards actually the same card?
posts.post_content:
Hi Guys,

Is the card on Ebay legitimate? Thoughts?

Thanks! 

[url]https://www.ebay.com/itm/1909-T206-George-Davis-120-White-Borders-PSA-7/373373296991?hash=item56eec8615f:g:SogAAOSwa6Jfxhch[/url]

[url]https://memorylaneinc.com/site/bids/bidplace?itemid=21651[/url]

Looks like the winner of the first auction is now selling it and making a decent profit for 2 months time. But yes, it's the same card. But that first auction ended nearly 2 months ago. If they were both current auctions running with the same card, then I'd be concerned.

Thanks! I was concerned by the apparent missing pixel on his hat (Ebay) and the light spot to the right of his body (on the Ebay version as well). The first auction (link two) occurred in 2011, right? What occurred two months ago? 

Thanks again!!

[quote name="tbr5020" post=2042509]Thanks! I was concerned by the apparent missing pixel on his hat (Ebay) and the light spot to the right of his body (on the Ebay version as well). The first auction (link two) occurred in 2011, right? What occurred two months ago? 

Thanks again!![/QUOTE]

It's the same card. Your right though on the end date. I was looking at the top left of the page, which must have been their last auction they had. But yes, it ended in 2011. So maybe not a huge return for the time past, but the auction isn't over yet. 7 watchers and everyone loves to bid at the last second. Hope he pulls a good profit for his time in the card. That spot is probably just glare. The phone or camera was too close to the card when taking the picture. It's better to be one to two feet away from the card and then zoom in, to avoid reflections and blurry photos.
